**CALLING ALL PROFESSIONAL DANCERS! YOUR NEW SIDE HUSTLE!**

**RE:SCULPT â€“ Instructor Auditions | London**

** **

**Think youâ€™ve got the fire to lead from the front?**

Weâ€™re on the hunt for instructors who bring serious energy, bold vibes, and unstoppable presence to every RE:SCULPT class. This is your chance to join a brand thatâ€™s shaking up the fitness industry and setting new standards for what a reformer-inspired strength workout can be.

At RE:SCULPT, we donâ€™t just teach classes - we *create experiences.* Youâ€™ll need to lift the room, command the energy, and connect with clients through every beat and every move. Youâ€™ll coach with precision, motivate with purpose, and deliver a workout that keeps clients coming back for more.

 

Weâ€™re looking for instructors who:
* Have undeniable stage presence and confidence on the mic.
* Understand how to blend performance with purpose - ensuring every workout has a vibe and is technically strong.
* Can create awesome energy while maintaining control and flow with the beat of the music.
* Can embrace the RE:SCULPT brand, values and community.

In return, we offer industry-leading training in the RE:SCULPT method, ongoing coaching development, and the opportunity to be part of our first **London** studio launch near **Battersea.**

Auditions are coming soon - and trust us, spots are limited.
High standards. Huge opportunity.

 

Is this for you?

Email your CV, highlighting relevant qualifications and experience, to headcoach@resculptstudios.co.uk

 
* *YOU NEED A MINIMUM OF A LEVEL 2 FITNESS QUALIFICATION, OR A PROFESSIONAL DANCE BACKGROUND.*
* *A PILATES QUALIFICATION IS NOT REQUIRED.*
* *AVAILABILITY FOR AT LEAST 2 â€œBLOCKSâ€ OF CLASSES PER WEEK*

Hello All! We are currently seeking 11 people to cast for a project featuring the internet sensation Sturniolo Triplets! We prefer individuals (Male) who have a similar stature to the triplets, around 5'8 ", slim, and 18 years or older, though applicants of any ethnicity are welcome.

The shoot is scheduled for Monday from 11 AM to 4 PM in West Hollywood. Although this gig is unpaid, it offers a valuable opportunity to be featured in a high-profile video, and food will be provided.

If anyone is interested, please let me know. They can contact me at campbellchae@gmail.com. Thank you!

CASTING CALL - PAID MUSIC VIDEO - LOS ANGELES

Project: Music Video Role: ELI (Supporting Lead) Rate: Paid Gig Shoot Date: Monday, October 20 Location: Los Angeles Area 

We are casting the supporting lead role of ELI for a narrative music video. We are looking for an actor who can portray a complex, dramatic arc.

ROLE: ELI

 â€¢ Gender: Male

 â€¢ Playing Age: Early 20s (character is a "twenty year old troublemaker" )

 â€¢ Look: "Scrappy kid with an easy smile" , "grungy but soft". We are looking for someone with a distinct look, similar to the provided reference photos (alt/skater vibe, expressive features).

 â€¢ Character Arc: This role requires significant emotional range.

 â—¦ Eli begins as a "playful" , charming boyfriend with a "laid-back grin". He and his girlfriend, Bridge, share a "quiet, tender" relationship. However, beneath the surface, he has a "well of self-doubt" that deepens into a "violent, paranoid descent".

 â—¦ The actor must be able to portray this "unraveling" , going from "sweet to scary" as his paranoia and pain warp him into something "unrecognizable-twisted, dangerous, and broken".ï¿½

REQUIREMENTS:

 â€¢ Must have strong dramatic acting ability to portray a "violent, paranoid descent" and "quiet unraveling".

 â€¢ Must be comfortable with MAKEUP. The role involves styling and makeup (eyeshadow) to create a "demonic" , "decaying" vibe as the character transforms.

 â€¢ Must be fully available for the shoot date (Monday, Oct. 20) in the Los Angeles area.

TO SUBMIT:

Please send the following to PINKMOOSECASTING@GMAIL.COM with the subject line: "MUSIC VIDEO CASTING - ELI - PLAYIN EXORCISTâ€

 1 Headshot and Resume

 2 Demo Reel (if available, please highlight any dramatic roles)

 3 A recent photo (selfie is fine)

 4 Confirmation of your availability for Monday, October 20th

Thank you! We look forward to seeing your submissions.

# **SANTA WORK AT HERTFORDSHIRE ZOO**
## ðŸŽ…**Be Our Santa at Hertfordshire Zoo!**ðŸŽ…

Hertfordshire Zoo is looking for jolly, enthusiastic, and festive individuals to bring the magic of Christmas to life this year as Santa Claus at **Hertfordshire Zoo in Broxbourne, Hertfordshire.**

Youâ€™ll be the star of our popular Christmas event, spreading joy and cheer to families visiting the zoo. From welcoming excited children to listening to Christmas wishes, youâ€™ll create unforgettable memories in our enchanting grotto.

**What Weâ€™re Looking For:**
* A warm, friendly personality with plenty of festive spirit
* Confidence interacting with children and families
* Reliability and professionalism
* Previous performance or grotto experience (preferred but not essential)

**When Youâ€™ll Work:**
* 29th & 30th November
* 6th & 7th December
* 13th & 14th December
* 20th, 21st, 22nd, 23rd & 24th December

**PLEASE NOTE** - You are not required to be available to work on all of these dates. Any availability is accepted.

Shifts will be approximately 8 hours per day.

**What We Offer:**
* A fun and rewarding role in a magical setting
* Â£22.50 per hour
* Full costume and training provided
* The chance to work at one of Hertfordshire's most loved attractions

If youâ€™ve got a hearty â€œHo Ho Ho!â€ and would love to make Christmas unforgettable for our visitors, weâ€™d love to hear from you.

Apply now by emailing **entertainment@hertfordshirezoo.com**

MY MOMMAâ€™S ERA: THE MUSICAL â€“ SEEN THROUGH MY MOTHERâ€™S LENS

Saturday, November 8, 2025
Greenwood Oasis Theater â€“ 7621 S. Greenwood Ave, Chicago, IL
Showtime: 7 PM | VIP Experience: 4 PM | Doors Open: 6 PM
FREE PARKING

Come dressed in your best 40s, 50s, 60s, or 70s attire!
(Itâ€™s recommended â€” not required â€” for the full experience!)

Step back in time and experience a powerful musical journey through the Great Migration, Bronzevilleâ€™s rich Black history, and the soul of World War II-era Chicago â€” told through acting, singing, dancing, and narration.

 Featuring unforgettable portrayals of:
Billie Holiday, Nat King Cole, Ella Fitzgerald, Dinah Washington, Cab Calloway, Etta James
Plus a moving tribute to Minnie Riperton, Chicagoâ€™s own.

A dynamic cast. Real stories. Legendary music.
This is more than entertainment â€” itâ€™s edutainment.

TICKETS & GROUP BENEFITS
Group rates (10+) already discounted online

items.text:
PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS â€” NOW SEEKING FINAL CREW MEMBERS

**Weâ€™re bringing a few more people aboard an already full production team for George Orwellâ€™s *****1984*****, directed by M.A.C.**

Weâ€™re looking for:
* **Assistant Producer**
* **Social Media / Marketing** Manager
* **Sound Board Operator**
* **Lighting Board Operator**

Performances run **December 4â€“7, 2025** at **Three Stories Theater (937 Liberty Ave, Downtown Pittsburgh)**.

Our **cast and crew of over 30 artists** are already deep in rehearsals and production work, and our design team has fully built out the world of the show. Weâ€™re looking for a few final team members to join the effort and help bring this ambitious production to completion.

**ASSISTANT PRODUCER**

Supports the Executive Producer with logistics, communications, scheduling, and coordination across departments. Ideal for someone organized, proactive, and interested in hands-on producing experience in a professional theatre environment.

**SOCIAL MEDIA / MARKETING MANAGER**

Join our marketing team to help manage social channels, coordinate content posting, and support our show rollout.
We already have **two resident photographers/videographers** and a **backlog of content ready to be edited, polished, and posted**. Youâ€™ll be shaping how this production is presented to the public.

SOUND & LIGHTING BOARD OPERATORS

We have professional **sound and lighting designers** who have already built out the showâ€™s systems and cues â€” weâ€™re simply looking for **two operators** to put that design work into action during **tech week and performances**.
Experience with QLab (for Sound) or ETC lighting consoles (for Lighting) is helpful, but a good sense of focus and teamwork is most important.

**COMPENSATION TYPE:** Volunteer / Possible post-show stipend
*(We want to be transparent: these are volunteer positions, but if funds allow, a small stipend may be available after the production.) *

**DATES & COMMITMENTS:**
* **Rehearsals (for reference):** Sundays, 6â€“9 PM starting August 3, 2025
Trust Arts Education Center â€” 807 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA
* **Tech Week:** November 24 â€“ December 3, 2025 (dark day on Thanksgiving)
* **Performances:** December 4â€“7, 2025 (5 performances total)
Three Stories Theater â€” 937 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA

Weâ€™re happy to work with your schedule â€” please share any known conflicts when reaching out.

**TO APPLY**
Please email **playboxpgh@gmail.com** with:
* Resume (or a brief note on your experience and interest)
* Availability during tech week and performances

If it seems like a good fit, weâ€™ll be in touch right away!

Thank you,
Marc Palombo
**PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS**

items.text: Iâ€™d love to pursue being an actress! At one point I was apart of a company that worked with actors/actresses. I also had representation at one point. However unfortunately I had to leave due to financial difficulties. They wanted me to get a natural representation, but the whole trip/experience would be close to $5k. Any suggestions, help, tips, or someone even who would consider being a manager for me?

topComments.text:
Hey Alicia Violeta Encinias - very sorry to hear that - what do you mean by natural representation ? Acting training ? General American accent training or a casting director workshop? 

My friendly advice is to whilst you are looking for an agent/manager is to find acting classes that will help keep your craft practiced - and yes we do sometimes invest in our career every once in a while, but the general rule has always been , donâ€™t pay for representation ( having an agent ) and also - donâ€™t invest what you donâ€™t have now , 

Iâ€™d love to ask you more - details like , do you have a demo reel, resume, which country you are at - but Iâ€™m open to listen and see what o can advise you on in a conducive manner â€” all the best !

You donâ€™t pay for representation. Thatâ€™s a scam. Any reputable agent/manager will pick you & get paid a commission from your pay if a casting director decides to pay you. 

An agent or manager takes you on their books because you fill a gap, a type that they need & which they believe is in demand. 

Do you have a CV & professional headshots and a showreel? If you have had professional jobs put together a CV. 

The most cost effective way to train yourself is to join a community theatre (unpaid, I realise, & not for a CV but great for doing & getting experience of a range of shows, making sure you can quickly learn lines and blocking and accept direction.)

Learn the difference between stage and screen acting. Above all do your research and due diligence. 

There are lots of people wanting to take money from would be professionals for courses which lead nowhere. 

Find out the courses which end with an actorsâ€™ showcase for reputable agents. 

Find out which are the reputable industry casting directory websites which casting directors use. 

If you are a triple threat (singing, acting, dancing) you may be able to get professional work quickly entertaining seniors, singing at events, in hotels, cabarets etc. As well as researching, network with other actors, directors, filmmakers & learn about the industry from them & possible openings. 

It is a very competitive industry filled with possible pitfalls and people who have trained from very young. 

Learn about screen acting (lots of videos, books as well as courses) & approach local colleges which have filmmaking courses where you may be cast in student films. 

Join new writing groups which need actors to read out scripts. You may find this leads to being cast in some productions of new scripts & again you can network and get tips. 

Financial difficulties are part and parcel often of an acting career so if you can have a side trade that will be helpful. 

It can help an actor to do backstage work: skills in make up, design, lighting, sound, stage management, assistant directing - it all feeds into acting and gives an overall view. 

Join a union when you can - again you can draw on the wealth of experience there, they can help you with looking over contracts, advising you generally on your career. 

Watch out for red flags when asked to pay up front. 

Iâ€˜m a writer in the UK  so Iâ€˜m sure there are others here who can advise you with much more with an overview of the US industry. 

Are you able to do a reputable full time training course? In the UK there is one casting website all professional actors must be on & qualify for if they want an agent and be seen by casting directors and I am sure others should be able to advise here of US situation. 

I hope this is helpful. It may help to put at least your general location. 

You will definitely need headshots, a CV and showreel. If you join a new writing group, you may find other actors who wish to do a filmed scene for their showreel and a writer and filmmaker who are willing to do it with you. Especially since Covid, all actors need to know how to do self tapes for auditions & actors can also do monologue or even duologue self tapes for showreels. 

Above all donâ€˜t rush in but do your research and network as well as doing as much stage, film as possible to gain experience, read lots of scripts, watch lots of stage & screen. If you can do a full time course with a good qualification at the end (again research, research, research & network, network, network to get recommendations), that would be a good springboard. Be careful about private responses to your social media posts - lots of scams & dangers - your local stage venues may also have worthwhile groups & opportunities. 

When you network you can create your own opportunities. 

Good luck!

ðŸ“£ðŸŽ¬ CASTING CALL - Short Period Drama 

We are casting for The Stuntman, a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 10th November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:
Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. With his fiancÃ©e Alice by his side, Ed stages one last ambitious stunt in the hope of saving his cinema - and their livelihood. A warm yet bittersweet drama about determination, passion and the march of technological change.

Roles:
Ed Morris (Lead, 28)
Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but hiding a quiet desperation as he struggles to keep silent film alive. Needs strong screen presence and subtle emotional depth.

Alice Fardon (Lead, 22â€“23)
Edâ€™s fiancÃ©e. Feisty, loyal, and practical. She supports his dreams but occasionally shows frustration at his all-consuming determination.

Community Extras
Townsfolk gathering to watch Edâ€™s big stunt. A mix of ages. Families, workers and individuals. To capture the atmosphere of a 1920s local community.

Apply by: 1st November 2025
To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Please include in email subject: THE STUNTMAN & NAME

After the success of our last workshop we're running another at the end of this month.

Actors are you looking to earn good money between acting gigs that also keeps your skills sharp? Get paid to travel the word and even fly business class? This is all possible in the lucrative world of roleplay, where your transferable skills as an actor make you an incredibly valuable asset in the world of training and development.

Act One Roleplay has over forty years combined experience, working domestically and internationally, across a whole host of industries and law enforcement agencies such as the CIA and UK Counter Terrorism. Our team have facilitated workshops and roleplayed across five continents, playing a part in making positive change whilst earning a good living.

We will be running our three-hour workshop, Introduction to Roleplay; Witness and Suspect Interviewing on Saturday the 31st of October from 1-4pm at Theatre Deli, in central London priced at Â£60.

The workshop is a starters guide to the world of roleplay and what it can offer you. In small groups, we cover the theoretical aspects of the work before putting it into practice. This is then followed by a Q&A session, meaning participants leave the session armed with an immersive experience and confident in starting their roleplay journey.

If youâ€™re interested in taking part in this or any future workshops, please contact us info@actoneroleplay.com

media.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'JANUARY, 1945. A young American soldier- Private Eddie Slovik awaits execution for the crime of desertion. As dawn approaches, the men ordered to carry out the sentence are forced to confront the weight of their duty. Loyalties fracture. Tempers flare. Morality is tested to breaking point, but who bears the greater burden: the deserter, or the ones tasked with ending his life? Inspired by real events, this taut and powerful drama explores the unseen toll of war on those who are told to follow orders, no matter the cost.'

items.text:
Hi, everyone.
Just wanted to invite you all to be part of my group for all alternative artists. I created this group with the intention of bringing together people from all backgrounds and areas of expertise to help each other create the projects we most desire. 
Although we are mostly numbered by filmmakers, as it encompasses many different skills, we're hoping for all artists to join. We hope to create a space where we can be mutually beneficial to each members' creativity and help bring our projects to life with our collective efforts.
Most members are based in the south of the UK, but we're happy for anyone to join and collaborate remotely where possible. 
Feel free to ask any questions and I'll leave a link in the comments.

items.text:
Mickey Mouse Horror Short Film
Hello, I am currently producing a Mickey Mouse Short film, with the working title, The Mouse Killer, which may become the actual title. 

This film is apart of my two existing films, My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh 1 and 2. This serves as the next chapter within the series, that will lead into the 3rd and final My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh film. 

Film Synopsis: two women are out in the woods, hunting down a mythical creature known as, Steamboat Willie, or Willie. 

If it all works out, this short film will be the start of a trilogy of short films. With the final one leading up to My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh 3.

Actors Age Range: 21 to up.

Looking for two females who can play the roles.

Compensation: none

Location: Fort Collins Colorado 

If you're interested, send me a message!

items.text:
Title: Forever Home

Genre: Horror/Thriller

Logline: A young couple tours their dream home with an unsettling real estate agent, only to discover the house holds a dark secret.

Roles:

-Raymond Russo

Age: 45-60

Gender: Male

Ethnicity: White

Description: A veteran real estate agent with a polished exterior. He is charming, articulate, and seemingly trustworthy. Beneath the polished exterior, however, is something deeply unsettling.

Requirements: Actor must be skilled with subtle menace and controlled delivery. Suited look; sharp features a plus.

-Susan

Age: 25-35

Gender: Female

Ethnicity: Any

Description: An optimistic, curious young woman whoâ€™s excited about starting a new chapter with her husband. Sheâ€™s practical yet impulsive when her curiosity is piqued.

Requirements: Needs range from natural warmth to terror. Must handle emotional intensity and physical acting in horror scenes.

Production Type: Indie

Contact Information: [luke@lostefilms.com](mailto:luke@lostefilms.com)

Run Time: Short

Compensation: Paid

Union Status: Non-union

Audition Information: Please email headshot, resume and demo reel to email provided (luke@lostefilms.com). We will send a copy of the script and audition instructions.

Shooting Schedule: One short shoot day must happen as soon as possible to capture the brief exterior scenes before leaves are all gone. The other full shoot day will be scheduled close to the exterior shoot day.

Filming Location: Denver metro area

Looking forward to your submissions!

CU DENVER STUDENT FILM CASTING CALL

Title: *Mannequins*

Genre: Thriller/Horror

Written and Directed by Archer Beck

Produced by Owen Etter

Logline: In a world where otherworldly invaders have forced humanity to live out a sitcom for their entertainment, the daughter figure in a mismatched family of strangers attempts to escape from her lifelong suburban prison.

Synopsis: In a carefully manufactured sitcom world, Daughter begins to see cracks in the illusion of her perfect family life. While she dreams of escaping the endless loop of canned laughter and staged dinners, Father insists they obey their unseen creators and preserve the familyâ€™s image at all costs. Their clash escalates into open rebellionâ€”until Mother, torn between them, helps Daughter break free. Outside the safety of their household, however, Daughter discovers a world ruled by an even stranger, otherworldly powerâ€”and must decide whether freedom is worth the price of losing the only family sheâ€™s ever known.

Main Roles: 

**Daughter **(16-18): Eldest daughter figure who is hellbent on escaping and finding answers.

**Father **(40s): Head of the household who is trying to keep the family unit obedient to the alien conquerors that control them.

**Mother **(40s): Silent caretaker of the family.

**Son **(8-10): Golden child of the household.

Location: Denver Area

Film Title: Clouds Have Bridges Too

Production Company: Wishing Tree Creatives

Director: Wanphrang Diengdoh (award-winning filmmaker)

Featuring: Adil Hussain

Location: Private home in Hertford

Shoot Date: Late October/ November (TBC)

Duration: Approx. 1â€“2 hours

Role & Requirements

Baby of mixed heritage or person of colour

Ideally: light brown skin, dark hair, dark eyes

Age: 12â€“18 months

The baby will portray the child of an Indian father and a White British mother

Scene involves only shots of the baby sleeping in a cot/bassinet

No outdoor scenes, no demanding or stressful filming â€” just peaceful, indoor filming in a gentle, quiet home environment

What We Provide & Expect

Paid role for 1â€“2 hours

Parents/carers must be present at all times â€” and are warmly welcomed on set

Calm, safe set with full health & safety protocols â€” babyâ€™s well-being is the top priority

We ensure breaks, a comfortable temperature, and minimal crew

If you have a baby basket or bassinet, let us know â€” it may be used for the scene

To Apply:

Please email enquiries@wishingtreecreatives.com with:

1ï¸âƒ£ Babyâ€™s name, age & heritage

2ï¸âƒ£ A few recent photos (in natural light)

3ï¸âƒ£ Your contact details & location

4ï¸âƒ£ Whether you can bring a cot or bassinet

Weâ€™re creating something gentle and beautiful â€” your babyâ€™s comfort and safety will always come first.

Wishing Tree Creatives

We are looking for 1 model for a restaurant photoshoot in Chester on Wednesday 8th October. The photos and videos will be used on the restaurantsâ€™ website & social media to showcase the experience of the venue.

Please comment below if you are available and meet the criteria for the shoot:
 
ðŸ“† Date: Wednesday 8th October. 
â° Time: 12pm-4pm
 
Requirements:
 
-       Age: Between 21-30
-       Female
-       Wearing casual outfit. 
- some playful tiktoks will also be filmed, so you must be comfortable with playful /sassy content (e.g like this: https://www.instagram.com/reel/DI4rOAITfbP/?igsh=MXd6cXFyaWtqdDdpMg==
 
ðŸ’¸ Compensation:
-       We have the budget to offer each model Â£125 for the few hours. 
- Food & drinks will be provided. 
 
More in-depth briefing will be given to those selected.
 
Please comment below if you are available and meet the criteria for the shoot and we will be in touch via Facebook DMs.

Hello,  I need a few more extras/ people for the upcoming film, My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh 2. Here are the list of scenes I need an extra for

Date Scene: this scene takes place at the start of the film, where the main character is trying to go on a date with a female, but the date dosent go well. 

Killed By Pooh Scene: need some people to be killed off by Pooh.

Killed By Rabbt Scene: need some people to be killed by Rabbit

I don't need alot of people, but a few could help make thos film perfectðŸ‘Œ the film is set to release November 21st 

Compensation: None

Location: Fort Collins  Colorado 

Let me know if you are interested!

Title: Trustmark

Role: Asian Toddler, 2-4 years old.

Production Type: Commercial

Contact Information: Casting@StoneCasting.TV

Compensation: $4000

Union Status: Non-union

Audition Information: Please email a recent selfie/headshot of toddler to Casting@StoneCasting.TV along with name, age and contact info.

Shooting Schedule: 11/3-10 (one or two days)

Filming Location: Denver, CO

Please feel free to share this notice with anyone you know whose child meets this casting spec.

- Thank you! - Stuart and Matt

sharedPost.text:
UPDATE: THESE ROLES HAVE BEEN FILLED!

BIRMINGHAM, ALABAMA area
FEATURE FILM
STAND-IN CASTING CALL
-----------------------------
Project: FEATURE FILM - "End The Wait"

Shoot Location: BIRMINGHAM, AL area
--MUST be able to work in the Birmingham, AL area as a LOCAL HIRE!! (Travel/Transportation/Accommodation will not be provided)

DATES NEEDED:  --Monday thru Friday--
MONDAY 10/13/25 -to- THURSDAY 11/13/25
-we do NOT have exact Call/Wrap times, so you should have FULL day/night available to allow for whatever the Call/Wrap Times end up being. **MUST HAVE FULL OPEN AVAILABILITY EVERY DAY Monday - Friday to be able to work every week day as needed

NON-UNION
Rate of PAY:  $175.00 for up to 12 hours (may not work that many hours but you will be paid for the full day even if you get wrapped sooner than 12 hours)  Overtime after 12 hours (if applicable)
_______________________________________________________
ROLES: **STAND-INS**
[CAUCASIAN STAND-IN] Male or Female, Caucasian, age range 20-60, height and weight not as important as long as you have previous Stand-in experience which is REQUIRED. You would be standing in for both our Male and Female Caucasian lead actors

[AFRICAN AMERICAN STAND-IN] Male or Female, African American, age range 20-60, height and weight not as important as long as you have previous Stand-in experience which is REQUIRED. You would be standing in for both our Male and Female African American lead actors
_______________________________________________
TO SUBMIT for these roles: 
Please send us an email ASAP to - onlocationcasting1@gmail.com 
With subject line BIRMINGHAM STAND-IN
Emails must include ALL of the following:   
-First & Last Name
-Phone Number
-Email Address
-Height 
-Weight 
-Clothing and Shoe Sizes 
-Current City/State you are located in
-CONFIRM you are fully available EVERY week day from 10/13 to 11/13 in Birmingham, AL
--Please provide a resume and/or a brief description of your Stand-in experience (project, actor, length of time - please don't just say "Yes I have Standin experience")
-Recent Color Photos of you (prefer cell phone photos rather than professional headshots - NO FILTERS!) . Please include at least (2) photos - (1) Close up and (1) Full Body Standing (make sure you are the ONLY person in your photo, no sunglasses or hats)

media.ocrText: No photo description available.

sharedPost.text:
ATLANTA, GA area
REALITY SERIES
FEATURED TALENT CASTING CALL
-----------------------------
Project: REALITY SERIES - Courtroom Project

Shoot Location: ATLANTA, GA area (Dunwoody)
--MUST be able to work in the Atlanta/Dunwoody, GA area as a LOCAL HIRE!! (Travel/Transportation/Accommodation will not be provided)

DATE NEEDED:  
SATURDAY 10/18/25
-we do NOT have exact Call/Wrap times, so you should have FULL day/night available to allow for whatever the Call/Wrap Times end up being. 

NON-UNION
Rate of PAY:  $150 for up to 8hours (may not work that many hours but you will be paid for the full day even if you get wrapped sooner than 8 hours)  
_______________________________________________________
ROLES: **Featured TALENT**
[COURTROOM PARTICIPANTS] Male and Female, age range 21-70 years old, all ethnicities, wide variety of types, MUST have some type of IMPROV ability or be able to "make up" dialogue on the spot to create certain courtroom situations. You will be presented with different scenarios and expected to create effective and realistic communications and arguments.  Some scenarios will require heightened emotions.
_______________________________________________
TO SUBMIT for these roles: 
Please complete the form at: https://forms.gle/dVmYF8vPFiSUYmUu7
--or-- if you are not able to upload to the google form, send us an email ASAP to - onlocationcasting1@gmail.com 
With subject line COURTROOM Series 10/18
Emails must include ALL of the following:   
-First & Last Name 
-Phone Number
-Email Address
-Height 
-Weight 
-Clothing and Shoe Sizes 
-Current City/State you are located in
-CONFIRM you are fully available on Saturday 10/18 in Atlanta, GA
-Recent Color Photos of you (prefer cell phone photos rather than professional headshots - NO FILTERS!) . Please include at least (2) photos - (1) Close up and (1) Full Body Standing (make sure you are the ONLY person in your photo, no sunglasses or hats)
**Please ALSO include a short self-tape video (can be from your phone) - tell us your first & last name and then act out a short improvised courtroom scenario. (If file is too large to send as an attachment, please send via WeTransfer or Dropbox and NOT as a youtube link!)
